                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#57vb">Fol. 57vb-58</locus>rb: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Partly in Amharic, crudely written in pencil in a secondary hand and hardly readable. The note mentions that the book was donated by ras Gäbrä Mädhǝn to the church Qärsäbär Mikaʾel in Ṭǝrr 13 (?) [19]39 A.M. (= January 1946 A.D.) during the time of Ḫaylä Śǝllase I (r. 1930-74) and Bishop Marqos (r. 1937-1951, as Bishop of Tǝgray and Eritrea).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude note in pen: fol. 4v.&#xD;
- Crude notes written in the margins: fols. 10v, 17v. &#xD;
- Pen trials: fol. 58v.</item>
